                                        <condition ana="fragments.contig">
                                             <p>The stone - polished on one side, the other being undressed and formless - is broken into three pieces, considerably differing in size but joining together with hardly any pieces missing. To date, pieces have not been joined permanently. The main break starts ca. 40 cm from the bottom on the right, slants down to the left, and ends ca. 25 cm from the bottom on the left. A secondary break is found at the right top of the lower piece, creating a sharp-angled triangle (measuring 7 x 25 x 23 cm), its tip pointing to the left.</p>
